==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Occultation
<hw>Oc`cul*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>occultatio</ets> a hiding, fr. <ets>occultare</ets>, v. intens. of
<ets>occulere</ets>: cf. F. <ets>occultation</ets>. See
<er>Occult</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>The hiding
of a heavenly body from sight by the intervention of some other of the
heavenly bodies; -- applied especially to eclipses of stars and planets
by the moon, and to the eclipses of satellites of planets by their
primaries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>(Fig.:)</mark> <def>The state of being
occult.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The reappearance of such an author after those long periods of
<qex>occultation</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Jeffrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Circle of perpetual occultation</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Circle</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Occulted</ent>⟦br⟧
